{"BRAG":[{"def":"To talk about one's self, or things pertaining to one's self, in a manner intended to excite admiration, envy, or wonder; to talk boastfully; to boast; -- often followed by of; as, to brag of one's exploits, courage, or money, or of the great things one intends to do.","pos":""}],"BRAGGADOCIO":[{"def":"A braggart; a boaster; a swaggerer.","pos":""},{"def":"Empty boasting; mere brag; pretension.","pos":""}],"BRAGGARDISM":[{"def":"Boastfulness; act of bragging.","pos":""}],"BRAGGART":[{"def":"O, I could play the woman with mine eyes, And braggart with my tongue.","pos":""}],"BRAGGER":[{"def":"One who brags; a boaster.","pos":""}],"BRAGGET":[{"def":"A liquor made of ale and honey fermented, with spices, etc.","pos":""}],"BRAGLESS":[{"def":"Without bragging.","pos":""}],"BRAGLY":[{"def":"In a manner to be bragged of; finely; proudly.","pos":""}]}